efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) for addAtHead/addAtTail, O(n) for get/addAtIndex/deleteAtIndex
space complexity: O(1) per operation
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a singly linked list with a size counter to enable O(1) tail insertion. All operations are straightforward pointer manipulations; the only O(n) operations are those that require traversal to a specific index.

